# Full-Stack Freelance Marketplace — Complete Integration Fix

## Problem Summary

The system is partially built but not functional:
- **Backend** uses in-memory C++ objects; SQLite DB exists ([Database.hpp](file:///c:/Users/Admin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/freelance_platform/backend/src/config/Database.hpp)) but routes in [main.cpp](file:///c:/Users/Admin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/freelance_platform/backend/main.cpp) never write to it
- **CMakeLists.txt** links MongoDB (not SQLite), so the build likely fails
- **Applications/Hire flow** entirely missing — no `/api/apply`, `/api/hire`, `/api/applications` endpoints
- **Frontend** [Clientprojects.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/freelance_platform/frontend/src/pages/Clientprojects.jsx) uses hardcoded mock data; [JobBrowsing.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/freelance_platform/frontend/src/pages/JobBrowsing.jsx) posts to `/api/bids` (mismatched endpoint)
